{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e26b12e7-0e7b-47ed-b733-ff36c514e5a9","content":"The template has the basic structure but has a few issues that should be addressed before publishing:\n\n**❌ Blocker: `choices` format is incorrect**\nThe `choices` property should be an array of objects, not a dictionary:\n```json\n\"choices\": [\n  { \"choice\": \"net8.0\", \"description\": \".NET 8\" },\n  { \"choice\": \"net9.0\", \"description\": \".NET 9\" }\n]\n```\n\n**⚠️ Recommended additions:**\n1. **`$schema`** — add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation\n2. **`groupIdentity`** — recommended for NuGet packages (e.g., `\"MyCompany.WebApi\"`)\n3. **`description`** — important for discoverability on NuGet\n\n**✅ Looks good:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `classifications`, `tags`, `sourceName` are all present and valid.\n\n**Verdict:** Not ready yet — fix the `choices` array format at minimum, and add `$schema`/`description` for a proper NuGet listing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"36b3f193-1d8d-4cba-8bd0-3b9d320e4cc0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check for required and recommended fields according to the .NET template engine specification.\n\nRequired fields:\n- `identity` ✓ - present\n- `name` ✓ - present\n- `shortName` ✓ - present\n\nMissing/issues:\n1. **`$schema`** - Missing. Best practice to include the schema reference for validation.\n2. **`groupIdentity`** - Missing. Recommended for NuGet packages that may contain multiple templates.\n3. **`precedence`** - Not strictly required but useful when multiple versions exist.\n\n\n4. **`preferNameDirectory`** - Not required.\n5. **`sourceName`** ✓ - present (used for name replacement)\n6. **`author`** ✓ - present\n7. **`classifications`** ✓ - present\n8. **`tags`** ✓ - present with language and type\n\nThe main blocker for NuGet publishing is the `choices` property format, which appears to be malformed and needs correction to work properly with the template engine. Looking at the official Microsoft template.json specification, the `choices` field definitely needs to be an array of objects with `choice` and `description` properties, not a dictionary format like what's currently in this file. The current structure would cause validation errors, so I need to flag this as incorrect and note that the `default` value is also missing. I'm seeing the schema URL that should be added to the template.json file, and now I'm reviewing the key issues I've identified: the missing `$schema` property for validation, the incorrect `choices` format that needs to be an array instead, and several recommended fields like `groupIdentity` and `description` that would improve the template's discoverability and organization on NuGet.","outputTokens":1319,"requestId":"1C17:19EA6:A9E45B4:B8A735C:69FD34EA"},"id":"64ee303a-b46d-4257-898e-9125d101464e","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:57:37.462Z","parentId":"babc3e16-15d8-4178-a125-453661e1eed3"}
